wikipedia_page.main: Julie Rayne is a British singer and entertainer, noted for her television appearances and recordings from the early 1960s.

response: Stars and Garters was a British television variety show produced by ATV from 1963 until 1965, set in a fictional public house. Hosted by comedian Ray Martine, regulars included singers Kathy Kirby, Vince Hill, Tommy Bruce, Al Saxon, Clinton Ford and Julie Rayne. Readers of Weekend magazine voted the show the Best TV Series of 1963.
